ENTRY            F1261   20260117   20260508   20260508       F108
SUBENT        F1261001   20260117   20260508   20260508       F108
BIB                 11         31
TITLE      Spin flip in the reactions S-32(p,p'gamma)S-32 and
           Ti-48(p,p'gamma)Ti-48
AUTHOR     (Van Syn Chan,Yu.V.Kangropol,A.Kapustsik,M.Madeya,
           G.M.Osetinskii,A.A.El Kamkhavi)
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB)
REFERENCE  (J,BAS,44,(1),43,1980) English translation
           (J,IZV,44,(1),53,1980)
           (C,78ALMAATA,,163,1978) Preliminary data are given.
REL-REF    (R,,J.W.Olness+,J,PR,112,1702,1958)
           (R,,P.G.Ikossi+,J,NP/A,274,1,1976)
           (R,,M.A.Eswaran+,J,PR/C,5,1270,1972)
           (R,,R.L.Kozub+,J,PR/C,5,413,1972)
           Spin, parity and resonance width values are given.
FACILITY   (VDG,4ZZZDUB)
INC-SOURCE Beam current was 0.1-0.2 mu-A. Irradiation time
           varied from 8 to 15 hours. Energy spread of the beam
           was 3.9 keV.
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) For proton registration three surface-barrier
           detectors were used. Energy resolution of detector
           was 35-40 keV for 5.49 MeV alpha-particles.
           (NAICR) For gamma-quanta detection photomultiplier
           with NaI crystal (50*60 mm) was used.
           Y-88 (Eg=1.84 MeV) source was used for determination
           of registration efficiency.
METHOD     (BCINT,COINC)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) Error of determination of detector efficiency
           (ERR-2) Uncertainty of beam current determination
           (ERR-S,5.,10.) Statistical error was 5% in resonance
           and 10% outside the resonance.
HISTORY    (20151111C)
           (20260117U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              31
COMMON               3          3
LVL-NUMB   ERR-1      ERR-2
NO-DIM     PER-CENT   PER-CENT
         1.        10.         1.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           38
SUBENT        F1261002   20260117   20260508   20260508       F108
BIB                  5          9
REACTION   (16-S-32(P,INL)16-S-32,PAR,DA,,REL)
           No explanation of relative units is given.
SAMPLE     Targets were prepared by evaporation of CdS onto thin
            (15-20 ug/cm2) self-supporting carbon films. The
           number of sulphur atoms was (2-3)*10**18 atoms/cm2.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR,,2.) Mean square error of angular
           distribution determination
STATUS     (CURVE,,Van Syn Chan+,J,BAS,44,(1),43,1980) Fig. 2
HISTORY    (20260117U) SD: BIB updated.
ENDBIB               9
